STRING FUNCTIONS

1. strlen();  // length of a string
	<?php
		echo strlen("Hello world!"); // outputs 12
	?>

2. str_word_count(); //counts the number of words
	<?php
		echo str_word_count("Hello world!"); // outputs 2
	?>

3. strrev();  //reverse of a string
	<?php
		echo strrev("Hello world!"); // outputs !dlrow olleH
	?>

4. strpos(string1, string2); // finds position of string2 in string 1
	If a match is found, the function returns the character position of the first match. If no match is found, it will return FALSE.

	<?php
		echo strpos("Hello world!", "world"); // outputs 6
	?>

5. str_replace(replace_this, with_this, in_this);
	<?php
		echo str_replace("world", "Dolly", "Hello world!"); // outputs Hello Dolly!
	?>